# Deadlock API Patterns

## Base URL

```js
const API_BASE = 'https://api.deadlock-api.com';
```

## Endpoints

| Endpoint | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `GET /v2/heroes` | Hero metadata (names, portraits) |
| `GET /v1/analytics/hero-stats?hero_id=<id>` | Win/loss counts |
| `GET /v1/analytics/hero-comb-stats?hero_id1=<id>&hero_id2=<id>` | Head-to-head matchup |
| `GET /v1/analytics/build-item-stats?hero_id=<id>` | Most-taken items |

## Hero Filtering

Only show heroes that are player-selectable and not in development:
```js
const playable = heroes.filter(h => h.player_selectable && !h.in_development);
```

## Winrate Calculation

```js
// From hero-stats response
const winRate = ((stats.wins / (stats.wins + stats.losses)) * 100).toFixed(1);
```

## Portrait URL

```js
const portrait = hero.images?.icon_image_small ?? '';
```

## Known Limitations

- Matchup data requires ≥ 50 matches; API returns empty array otherwise
- No per-hero item winrate data is available — only pick frequency
